   "source": [
    "In this first test, we used the scikit-multiflow library to create fake sensor data and check if the model can find unusual values (anomalies). We made 500 data samples using AnomalySineGenerator, which adds some random errors on purpose. Then, we used the HalfSpaceTrees model to learn and detect these errors. However, we trained and tested the model on the same data, so the model got confused and said almost everything was an anomaly. This is why, in the graph, the red line (predicted anomalies) stays high all the time. To fix this, we will train the model only on normal data first, and then test it on new data. This will help the model learn what normal looks like and find only the real problems.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
